Name: Scpqual
Title: pan-Canadian Provider Qualification Types
Description: SCPQUAL is used to encode the degree or educational rank of a healthcare provider credential as defined by the various Royal Canadian Professional Medical Collages. It is also supports the encoding “Expertise type” in the pan-Canadian version 3 messages

Name: AddressType
Title: AddressType
Description: The type of an address (physical / postal).

Name: AddressUse
Title: AddressUse
Description: The use of an address.

Name: AdministrativeGender
Title: AdministrativeGender
Description: The gender of a person used for administrative purposes.

Name: BundleType
Title: BundleType
Description: Indicates the purpose of a bundle - how it is intended to be used.

Name: ContactPointSystem
Title: ContactPointSystem
Description: Telecommunications form for contact point.

Name: ContactPointUse
Title: ContactPointUse
Description: Use of contact point.

Name: DaysOfWeek
Title: DaysOfWeek
Description: The days of the week.

Name: HTTPVerb
Title: HTTPVerb
Description: HTTP verbs (in the HTTP command line). See [HTTP rfc](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231) for details.

Name: IdentifierUse
Title: IdentifierUse
Description: Identifies the purpose for this identifier, if known .

Name: IssueSeverity
Title: IssueSeverity
Description: How the issue affects the success of the action.

Name: IssueType
Title: IssueType
Description: A code that describes the type of issue.

Name: LocationMode
Title: LocationMode
Description: Indicates whether a resource instance represents a specific location or a class of locations.

Name: LocationStatus
Title: LocationStatus
Description: Indicates whether the location is still in use.

Name: NameUse
Title: NameUse
Description: The use of a human name.

Name: OrganizationAffiliationRole
Title: Organization Affiliation Role
Description: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the role of one Organization in relation to another.

Name: ResourceType
Title: ResourceType
Description: One of the resource types defined as part of this version of FHIR.

Name: SearchEntryMode
Title: SearchEntryMode
Description: Why an entry is in the result set - whether it's included as a match or because of an _include requirement, or to convey information or warning information about the search process.

Name: SNOMED_CT
Title: SNOMED CT (all versions)
Description: SNOMED CT is the most comprehensive and precise clinical health terminology product in the world, owned and distributed around the world by The International Health Terminology Standards Development Organisation (IHTSDO).

Name: ContactEntityType
Title: Contact entity type
Description: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the purpose for which you would contact a contact party.

Name: LocationType
Title: Location type
Description: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the physical form of the Location.  This includes several 'non physical' codes which are still considered a location.

Name: OperationOutcomeCodes
Title: Operation Outcome Codes
Description: Operation Outcome codes used by FHIR test servers (see Implementation file translations.xml)

Name: BedStatus
Title: bedStatus
Description: Code system of concepts which specify the state of a bed in an inpatient setting, and is used to determine if a patient may be assigned to it or not.  Used in HL7 Version 2.x messaging in the DLD and PV1 segments.

Name: IdentifierType
Title: identifierType
Description: HL7-defined code system of concepts specifying type of identifier. Used in HL7 Version 2.x messaging data types CX, PLN, PPN, XCN and XON.

Name: Confidentiality
Title: Confidentiality
Description: A set of codes specifying the security classification of acts and roles in accordance with the definition for concept domain "Confidentiality".

Name: RoleCode
Title: RoleCode
Description: A set of codes further specifying the kind of Role; specific classification codes for further qualifying RoleClass codes.

Name: RoleStatus
Title: RoleStatus
Description: Codes representing the defined possible states of an Role, as defined by the Role class state machine.

Name: Ietf3066
Title: Tags for the Identification of Languages
Description: Older value from OID registry.  Superceded; see recommendations in BCP-47.
